%h2 The Presentation
%p The awesome team of Diana Mounter and Reem Abdelaty from the <a href="http://lgwebnetwork.org/">LGwebnetwork</a> asked if I would deliver the closing keynote for their first ever web conference, <a href="http://lgwebnetwork.org/conference/">WE Believe in Community</a>. I was honoured to accept.
%p I wanted to show people what I see in the web. What I see happening. Where I think everything is going. But I&rsquo;m a firm believer in showing people techniques and technologies they can use right now. All of which made it very easy for me to talk about the Open Web. There&rsquo;s an entire blog post I&rsquo;ve been meaning to write for a long time about that, so we won&rsquo;t get into it here. This is just to post my slides and to say that video and a podcast will be forthcoming at some point in the future. (I hear end of the week.)
%p 
  %strong Update: 
  <a href="http://lgwebnetwork.org/2008/09/04/local-government-on-the-open-web/">Video is now available</a>.

