%h2 The conference
%p Put together in only a few months to meet a pressing need for stronger networking and more formal professional development for local government web workers, the entire experience was amazing. Both Reem and Diana radiate energy and passion and they communicated this to every attendee. There was a huge buzz of engagement and involvement. It was a real privilege to be a part of it!
%p
  The other big win of the two days was the outstanding quality of the content.
  %span.vcard
    %a.fn.url{ :href => "http://westciv.typepad.com/dog_or_higher/", :rel => "met" } John Allsopp
  delivered a stirring opening keynote of what constitutes the web and how you can expect to access it going forward. He delivered some concepts I&rsquo;m going to be thinking about for a long time. I particularly enjoyed these quotes too:
%ul
  %li
    %cite &ldquo;the web just connects stuff together, do you really think you <strong>need</strong> a screen?&rdquo;; and
  %li
    %cite &ldquo;local government should be be building the networks, they&rsquo;re the sewers of the 21st century&rdquo;.
%p
  Another presentation that I really enjoyed was
  %span.vcard
    %a.fn.url{ :href => "http://magia3e.wordpress.com/", :rel => "acquaintance met" } Matthew Hodgson
  on
  %a{ :href => "http://magia3e.wordpress.com/2008/08/25/we-believe-in-communiuty/" } the death and rebirth of intranets
  \. He had a clever premise and great solid content that intertwined really well. He also managed to record himself, so he has audio up already! Unfortunately, I missed
  %span.vcard
    %a.fn.url{ :href => "http://www.ruthellison.com/", :rel => "acquaintance met" } Ruth Ellison&rsquo;s
  as she was just before me (and I was in the tea room doing the obsessive compulsive slide check), but she has her (and Adrian&rsquo;s) slides up already along with a
  %a{ :href => "http://www.ruthellison.com/2008/08/24/local-government-web-network-conference-2008-writeup/" } great summation of each presentation she saw
  \. There were lots of other great speakers, so hopefully they&rsquo;ll be putting their slides up soon too.
  
